author: gstein
msg: Continue the rejiggering of the log processing. Read the log contents
entirely into memory, rather than chunking it (we're about to switch to an
in-memory solution; this is a precursor).
This revision also adds workqueue processing when we run the logs.
(run_log): take a CANCEL_FUNC/BATON pair for passing along (the old
loggy doesn't like them so much, but some bits do). read the log
entirely into memory, and pass to expat. call wq_run() after all the
(svn_wc__run_log, svn_wc__run_log2): pass NULL for the CANCEL_FUNC and
(cleanup_internal): remove a ton of code that optimizes the cleanup
process, and just rely on run_log() to do it all.

author: rhuijben
msg: Partially revert r39860 to fix a few libsvn_ra_serf tests.
(svn_ra_serf__get_dir): Handle path as uri, or the path walker will not
